# Frontend Rules

## Stack

* ReactJS
* TypeScript
* Ant Design
* React Query
* Zustand
* React Router

---

## Folder Structure

src/

pages/
components/
layouts/
services/
hooks/
store/
types/
utils/
routes/

---

## Component Rules

Prefer:

* Functional Components
* Hooks
* Reusable Components

Avoid:

* Class Components
* Large Components >300 lines

---

## Page Structure

Each page:

* UI
* Hooks
* Service Calls

Business logic belongs inside:

* hooks
* services

---

## Data Fetching

Use React Query.

Never call axios directly inside components.

Use:

services/

Example:

patientService.ts

queueService.ts

paymentService.ts

---

## State Management

Use Zustand for:

* Auth
* User Profile
* Notification
* Global Settings

Use React Query for:

* API Data
* Server Cache

---

## UI Guidelines

Use Ant Design.

Preferred components:

* Table
* Card
* Drawer
* Modal
* Statistic
* Timeline
* Badge

---

## Dashboard Rules

Admin Dashboard must support:

* Heatmap
* Queue Monitoring
* Live Statistics
* Department Status
* Alerts

Use realtime Socket.IO updates.

---

## Performance

Use:

* React.memo
* Lazy Loading
* Code Splitting

Avoid unnecessary re-renders.
